            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Sami Haddad\u2019s sense of hospitality was ingrained long before he could pronounce \"Gew\u00fcrztraminer.\" Raised in Dearborn, Michigan, his childhood was a vibrant tapestry of Lebanese culture, centered around his parents\u2019 bustling kitchen. His family, who immigrated from Beirut in the 1990s, taught him that generosity was best expressed through food and drink. The Haddad home was the neighborhood hub, always filled with the aroma of roasting lamb and the warm chatter of guests, a lesson in service that Sami absorbed deeply.\n\nWhile pursuing his Hospitality and Tourism degree, he felt a pull toward something more specialized than hotel management. The turning point was a study abroad semester in Lyon, France. A day trip to a small, family-run vineyard in Beaujolais changed everything. The vintner spoke of soil and sunlight with the reverence of a poet, and a single glass of wine told a story spanning generations. Sami was captivated. He returned to the States with a new obsession, dedicating himself to the intricate world of wine.\n\nAfter graduation, San Francisco was the only logical destination. It was the epicenter of American culinary innovation, with Napa and Sonoma just a stone's throw away. He landed an entry-level position at a prestigious Financial District restaurant and quickly proved his palate was as sharp as his work ethic. Within two years, he was promoted to Sommelier, a point of immense pride.\n\nNow, Sami lives in a small but tidy apartment in North Beach, relishing the short, 0.8-mile walk past historic storefronts and cafes to his work. His days are for study\u2014poring over wine atlases and blind-tasting with fellow sommeliers\u2014and his nights are a performance. On the restaurant floor, he moves with quiet confidence, translating the complex language of the cellar into accessible joy for his guests. His social life is deeply intertwined with the industry, a close-knit group of chefs and servers who understand the demanding hours.\n\nSami\u2019s dream is fixed on the horizon: earning the coveted red pin of a Master Sommelier. He aspires to one day open his own wine bar, a place that marries the sophisticated terroir of California wine with the warm, unconditional hospitality he learned in his family's Michigan home."
